  <div class="help-header"><h2>Guild Name Generator Guide</h2><p>How to pick a guild name that raiders remember and name checkers approve.</p></div>
  <div class="help-grid">
    <div class="help-card"><h3>Step 1: pick a theme</h3><ol><li><strong>Fantasy</strong>: dragons, runes, emerald forests &mdash; WoW, FFXIV, Lost Ark.</li><li><strong>Sci-fi</strong>: orbital legions, nebula corsairs &mdash; Destiny 2, Eve Online, Star Citizen.</li><li><strong>Dark / evil</strong>: shadow covenants, cursed orders &mdash; antagonist roleplay.</li><li><strong>Noble / heroic</strong>: paladins, lions, radiant orders &mdash; Alliance, light-aligned factions.</li><li><strong>Rogue / outlaw</strong>: thieves, smugglers, crews &mdash; pirate / bandit fiction.</li><li><strong>Mythic / legendary</strong>: titans, ascendants, godhood &mdash; end-game elitist aesthetic.</li></ol></div>
    <div class="help-card"><h3>Step 2: pick a template</h3><ul><li><strong>Order of the X</strong>: classic paladin / clerical vibe (<em>Order of the Phoenix</em>).</li><li><strong>House of X</strong>: ASOIAF, royal roleplay (<em>House Ravenrock</em>).</li><li><strong>The Xs</strong>: short, sharp (<em>The Silent Daggers</em>).</li><li><strong>Adjective + Noun</strong>: two-word standard (<em>Crimson Wolves</em>).</li><li><strong>X of Y</strong>: evocative (<em>Reapers of Mordor</em>).</li><li>Or choose <em>Mix it up</em> to roll across all templates.</li></ul></div>
